spans.text: Let Gold , like Guilt , increase the Miser's Grief
The dull Narration of a tedious Muse
ends the Travel of the Day
sharpened Scythes the labouring Mowers wield
my Friend , to Charlton take my Way
No Cares , no Toils , no Troubles now appear ; For Troubles , Toils , and Cares
soon the chol'ric Fumes of Liquour
Some Hours of Rest sacred to TEMPLE's Name
the Muse to silver Kennet flies , On whose green Margin Hertford's Turrets rise

the lofty Height , Towns , Valleys , Rivers

JEHOVAH's Praise : Uncharmed with all the fluttering Pomp of Pride , Heaven , and domestic Care her Time divide : In her own Breast she seeks a calm Repose , And shuns the crowded Rooms of Belles and Beaux ; Where COQUETILLA oft her Eyes has rolled , Oft won a worthless Heart , and lost her Gold
shuns the crowded Rooms of Belles
to dwell , In verdant Beauties cannot these excel
His mellow Pipe , or vocal Music

the wanton Lambkins played , Whose artless Bleatings rural Music made ; Too harsh perhaps to please politer Ears , Yet much the sweetest Tune the Farmer hears

a Temple , drew the glorious Plan
makes the sacred Columns rise , And bids the lofty Spire invade the Skies

Ambition learn to cheque its Pride : High Stations often bring a Weight of Cares ; True Happiness is found in humble Spheres : This useful Truth let Sarum's Glory show , Which faded when on high , but flourishes below

a cooling Shade , Where BATHURST oft converses with the Dead
Nor trusts Tomorrow , but Today he lives
Eyes a Pile of Ruins rose
let me such cruel Faith approve
Christian Charity incline my Mind To wish the Happiness of all Mankind
my Mind To wish the Happiness of all Mankind
me live , Slow to be angry , easy to forgive

And now the Lawn , and winding Walks
Your sylvan Scenes , where future Navies
lofty Oaks their branching Arms extend , And towering Pines to
opening Glades admit the sunny Ray
Fops despise , And think of Actions worthy of the Wise
of Actions worthy of the Wise
Southampton , washed with THETIS' silver Waves
Intrepid Sailors , swarming in the Sky , Intent on Business , different Labours
Thick as the Insects , round the Poplar , play , When PHOEBUS
The daring Man , who tempts the foamy Wave
what ruthless Pains distressed Thy dizzy Head
did the Bard thy Fate bemoan
The smiling Glass , with rosy Liquour crowned , Sacred to friendly Healths ,
before The winged Castle ventures from the Shore
to fly Her first long Journey through the spacious Sky

VULCAN's heavenly Art to Mortals taught
to proper Time : Man's Bosom then sonorous Organs warmed , The softer Lyre his gloomy Sorrows charmed ; While Tyrants Hearts unusual Pity found , And savage Tempers softened with the Sound

loyal Healths the Captain pushes round
sweeter Flavour to the sparkling Wine
When fervid PHOEBUS burned his glowing Head
ten thousand Trees adorned the Plain , Ten thousand Shades , delightful to the Swain

an elegant Divine , In whom the Scholar , Friend , and Critic join ; Who freely judges of an Author's Thoughts , Improves his Beauties , and corrects his Faults ; Severely kind , and candidly severe ; Polite , as Courtiers ; and , as Truth , sincere ; Who , in MINERVA's Temple , taught our Youth The Path to Wisdom , Virtue , Honour , Truth ; Till having , with a generous Mind , bestowed The Flower of all his Years in doing Good ; Fatigued with Labours , and with Age decayed , Retires , with Honour , to the rural Shade
